---
import WebsiteLayout from '../../../layouts/WebsiteLayout.astro';

const title = "Don't Sleep, There Are Snakes";
const author = "Daniel Everett";
const pubYear = "2008";
const rating = 5;
const slug = "dont-sleep-there-are-snakes";
---

<WebsiteLayout>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <title>{title} by {author} - Book Review</title>
    <meta name="description" content={`Review of "${title}" by ${author}. Rating: ${rating}/5 stars.`} />
    <!-- Open Graph / Facebook -->
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="og:url" content={Astro.url.href} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={`${title} by ${author}`} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={`Review of "${title}" by ${author}. Rating: ${rating}/5 stars.`} />
    <!-- Twitter -->
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:url" content={Astro.url.href} />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content={`${title} by ${author}`} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={`Review of "${title}" by ${author}. Rating: ${rating}/5 stars.`} />
  </Fragment>

  <article class="book-review-content">
    <div class="book-header">
      <div class="book-meta">
        <h1 class="book-title">{title}</h1>
        <p class="book-author">By {author}</p>
        <p class="book-year">Published: {pubYear}</p>
        <div class="book-rating">
          {Array.from({ length: 5 }).map((_, i) => (
            <span class={`star ${i < rating ? 'filled' : ''}`}>★</span>
          ))}
          <span class="rating-text">{rating}/5</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="book-summary-section">
      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <p>
        A fascinating account of Everett's time living among the Pirahã people of the Amazon rainforest. 
        The book challenges fundamental assumptions about language, culture, and human cognition. Everett's 
        observations about the Pirahã language—which lacks numbers, colors, and recursion—forced him to 
        reconsider Chomsky's theory of universal grammar. Beyond linguistics, it's a deeply human story 
        about cultural immersion, the limits of Western thought, and what we can learn from radically 
        different ways of being.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="review-section">
      <button class="review-toggle" id="review-toggle">
        <span class="toggle-text">Show Review</span>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </button>
      <div class="book-review-collapsible" id="review-content">
        <h2>My Review</h2>
        <p>
          This book completely reshaped how I think about language, culture, and human cognition. Everett's 
          narrative is both deeply personal and rigorously scientific—he doesn't just report on the Pirahã, 
          he immerses you in their world.
        </p>
        
        <h3>What Struck Me Most</h3>
        <p>
          The Pirahã language challenges so many assumptions we take for granted. No numbers beyond "one," 
          "two," and "many." No color terms. No recursion—they can't embed clauses within clauses. This 
          isn't a deficiency; it's a different way of organizing reality. The Pirahã live in the "immediacy 
          of experience" principle—they only talk about things they've directly witnessed or that someone 
          they know has witnessed.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Everett's journey from missionary linguist to someone questioning his own faith and academic 
          assumptions is compelling. He went to convert the Pirahã, but they ended up converting him—not 
          to their religion (they don't have one), but to a deeper understanding of human possibility.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Linguistic Implications</h3>
        <p>
          The book ignited a major debate in linguistics. Chomsky's theory of universal grammar posits that 
          all languages share certain structural features. The Pirahã language, if Everett is correct, 
          challenges this. But more importantly, it raises questions about whether language shapes thought 
          or thought shapes language—or if the relationship is more complex than either extreme.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Cultural Insights</h3>
        <p>
          Beyond linguistics, the book offers profound insights into how different cultures organize reality. 
          The Pirahã's focus on immediate experience, their lack of creation myths, their egalitarian 
          social structure—all of this challenges Western assumptions about what's "natural" or "universal" 
          in human societies.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Criticisms & Questions</h3>
        <p>
          Some linguists have challenged Everett's claims, particularly about recursion. The debate continues, 
          but even if some of the linguistic claims are disputed, the cultural observations remain powerful. 
          The book raises important questions about how we study other cultures and whether we can truly 
          understand ways of being that are radically different from our own.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Final Thoughts</h3>
        <p>
          This is one of those books that changes how you see the world. It's not just about linguistics or 
          anthropology—it's about the limits of our own understanding and the possibility of radically 
          different ways of being human. Everett writes with humility, respect, and genuine curiosity. 
          Highly recommended for anyone interested in language, culture, or the nature of human cognition.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="related-section">
      <h2>Related Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Noam Chomsky - <em>Syntactic Structures</em> (for contrast with Everett's claims)</li>
        <li>Jared Diamond - <em>The World Until Yesterday</em> (on traditional societies)</li>
        <li>Wade Davis - <em>The Wayfinders</em> (on different ways of knowing)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="back-link">
      <a href="/books/have-read">← Back to Books I've Read</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</WebsiteLayout>

<style>
  .book-review-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  .book-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .book-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .book-title {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .book-author {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #4b5563;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .book-year {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .book-rating {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .star {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #e5e7eb;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .star.filled {
    color: #facc15;
  }

  .rating-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .book-review-content section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .book-review-content h2 {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .book-review-content h3 {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .book-review-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .book-review-content ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .book-review-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .review-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .review-toggle {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #f9fafb;
    border: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 8px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #0f172a;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .review-toggle:hover {
    background: #f3f4f6;
    border-color: #cbd5e1;
  }

  .review-toggle.active {
    border-bottom-left-radius: 0;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 0;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .toggle-icon {
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #6b7280;
  }

  .review-toggle.active .toggle-icon {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .book-review-collapsible {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s ease, padding 0.4s ease, margin 0.4s ease;
    padding: 0 1.25rem;
    margin: 0;
    background: #f9fafb;
    border: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-top: none;
    border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px;
  }

  .book-review-collapsible.expanded {
    max-height: 5000px;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .book-review-collapsible h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .back-link {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .back-link a {
    color: #2b6cb0;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .back-link a:hover {
    color: #1e40af;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .book-review-content {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }

    .book-title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .book-author {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .book-review-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .book-review-content h3 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    .book-review-collapsible.expanded {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const toggle = document.getElementById('review-toggle');
    const content = document.getElementById('review-content');
    
    if (toggle && content) {
      toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const isExpanded = content.classList.contains('expanded');
        
        if (isExpanded) {
          content.classList.remove('expanded');
          toggle.classList.remove('active');
          toggle.querySelector('.toggle-text').textContent = 'Show Review';
        } else {
          content.classList.add('expanded');
          toggle.classList.add('active');
          toggle.querySelector('.toggle-text').textContent = 'Hide Review';
        }
      });
    }
  });
</script>





